summary: LEO BURNETT U.S.A. was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature on December 12, 1984. The award was presented by President George H.W. Bush at the White House in Washington, D.C. It was the first ever Nobel Peace Prize awarded to a Nobel laureate.
